  "options": [
    {
      "id": "doubt_everything",
      "text": "If you were wrong about this, what else are you wrong about?",
      "description": "Your judgment clearly can't be trusted.",
      "resultText": "The failure of discernment spirals into broader self-doubt. You start questioning all your assessments, past and present. Did you ever really understand anything? The uncertainty is paralyzing. You stop trusting your own judgment entirely, either deferring to others or avoiding decisions altogether. It's safer to claim ignorance than to be proven wrong again. But the lack of confidence in your own perception is corrosive.",
