    {
      "id": "accept_limitations",
      "text": "Even good judgment fails sometimes",
      "description": "Being wrong doesn't mean you're incapable.",
      "resultText": "You acknowledge the failure without letting it destroy your confidence. Yes, your judgment was wrong this time. That doesn't mean it's always wrong, or that you should stop trusting yourself. You're human. Humans make mistakes. You process the disappointment, extract what lessons you can, and then move forward. Your discernment is temporarily clouded, but you know clarity will return. This isn't who you are; it's just a moment you're passing through.",
